    diagnostics: ["H. pylori testing: urea breath test (preferred non-invasive), stool antigen test, or serology; PPIs must be held 2 weeks and antibiotics/bismuth 4 weeks before breath or stool testing to avoid false negatives","Upper endoscopy (EGD) for alarm symptoms: dysphagia, unintentional weight loss, GI bleeding, persistent vomiting, iron deficiency anemia, age >55 with new-onset dyspepsia","Serum gastrin level if Zollinger-Ellison suspected (fasting gastrin >1000 pg/mL is diagnostic; 100-1000 pg/mL requires secretin stimulation test) -- must hold PPI for 1-2 weeks before testing","24-hour esophageal pH monitoring and impedance testing for refractory GERD (gold standard for measuring acid exposure)","CBC to assess for iron deficiency anemia from chronic GI blood loss or PPI-related malabsorption","Serum magnesium level for patients on long-term PPI therapy (>1 year), especially with concurrent diuretics"],
