      action: "Blocks both alpha-1 (vasodilation, reduces peripheral vascular resistance) and beta-1/beta-2 (reduces heart rate and cardiac output) adrenergic receptors; preferred antihypertensive in pregnancy due to established safety profile",
      sideEffects: "Orthostatic hypotension, fatigue, dizziness, nausea, nasal congestion, neonatal bradycardia if used near delivery",
