        correct: 2,
        rationale: "Labetalol is the first-line antihypertensive for chronic hypertension in pregnancy. ACE inhibitors (lisinopril) and ARBs (losartan) are absolutely contraindicated due to fetotoxicity (renal agenesis, oligohydramnios). Atenolol is associated with fetal growth restriction. Labetalol has an established safety profile across all trimesters."
