        correct: 1,
        rationale: "The FDA letter categories were replaced by the Pregnancy and Lactation Labeling Rule (PLLR) because they oversimplified complex, nuanced risk data into single letters, failed to distinguish between quality of evidence (human vs animal data), did not account for trimester-specific risks, and led to both unnecessary fear and false reassurance among prescribers and patients."
